| Build Funded First speed-to-lead | GHL → Vapi pipeline | vapi-phone-agent-use-cases |
| Wire call transcripts to Revenue Intel | Revenue Intelligence Engine | New |

---

## 3. Success Criteria

| Metric | Target | Measurement |
|--------|--------|-------------|
| AEO audit coverage | 5 brands tracked weekly | Monday cron output |
| Dispatch failure rate | <10% (down from ~25%) | agent_dispatch_bridge logs |
| Code review loop time | <3 iterations per PR | PR comment count |
| Vapi speed-to-lead | <30 seconds form-to-call | GHL → Vapi latency |

---

## 4. Dependencies & Risks

| Risk | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|
| Perplexity API deprecated in our stack (May 4) | Use OpenRouter sonar-pro endpoint instead |
| Vapi requires paid account for production | Start with free trial, evaluate before committing |
| Local LLM needs VPS RAM (8GB limit) | Defer to Phase 3+, use 7B models only |
| `local-llm-picker-skill` repo is private | Work from bundle description + L1B3RT4S repo instead |

---

## 5. Rollback Plan

Each phase is independently reversible:
- Phase 1: Skill files are additive (references/ folder). Delete to rollback.
- Phase 2: AEO app is a standalone Viktor Space. Remove Vercel project + Convex backend to rollback.
- Phase 3: Vapi integration is webhook-based. Disable GHL workflow to rollback.
